you can be pretty sure that
it's natural cocoa powder.

00:37:35.770 --> 00:37:39.550
And if it's baking soda,
baking powder, then it's

00:37:39.550 --> 00:37:41.360
Dutch process or alkalized.

00:37:41.360 --> 00:37:43.420
And then so everything's
in here now, right?

00:37:43.420 --> 00:37:46.180
All of the dry ingredients?

00:37:46.180 --> 00:37:49.030
And I whisk it, strain it.

00:37:49.030 --> 00:37:52.579
I call it sifting into the bowl.

00:37:52.579 --> 00:37:54.370
If you don't have whole
wheat pastry flour,

00:37:54.370 --> 00:37:58.170
you can just add up the amount
of flour and use all AP.

00:37:58.170 --> 00:38:02.340
And then the last step with all
these ingredients is to whisk.

00:38:02.340 --> 00:38:06.230
And then all the liquid
ingredients in another bowl.

00:38:06.230 --> 00:38:08.870
And I just don't
combine them until I

00:38:08.870 --> 00:38:11.970
know that the oven rack is
in the right place, which

00:38:11.970 --> 00:38:15.780
for a standard oven would be
the center, that the cake pan is

00:38:15.780 --> 00:38:19.470
greased, oiled, and a piece
of parchment on the bottom.

00:38:19.470 --> 00:38:21.080
And don't flip the
parchment over,

00:38:21.080 --> 00:38:25.197
and don't use flour
unless the recipe

00:38:25.197 --> 00:38:27.530
writer is telling you to do
it, but not with my recipes.

00:38:27.530 --> 00:38:29.420
I find it doesn't work.

00:38:29.420 --> 00:38:32.240
And then you're good to go,
and then put it in the oven.

00:38:32.240 --> 00:38:35.120
So if you don't have time,
it's like the phone rang

00:38:35.120 --> 00:38:38.280
or something, just don't
combine your batter.

00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:42.460
I do recommend everybody has an
oven thermometer in their oven

00:38:42.460 --> 00:38:45.490
because they vary
like crazy, right?

00:38:45.490 --> 00:38:50.440
I had a brand new oven,
and I set it to 350.

00:38:50.440 --> 00:38:52.380
